FOOT-AND-MOUTH DISEASE, SUSPECTED - ARGENTINA: PANAFTOSA REPLY
*************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
<http://www.fas.org/ahead/>
See Also
Foot & mouth disease, suspected - Argentina (Buenos Aires 990108134903
Foot & mouth disease, suspected - Argentina: NOT 990112101619
Date: Thu 14 Jan 1999
From: <woodall@bioqmed.ufrj.br>
The Director of PANAFTOSA, the Pan American Foot-and-Mouth Disease &
Zoonosis Center, has asked us to explain that they were NOT
responsible for the erroneous report of an outbreak of FMD in
Argentina which we posted and attributed to them, & that they do NOT
make errors in reporting facts -- see Spanish original of their
request below.
[As we have already explained, we made an error by omitting the
critical word "Simulation" from our translation of the report in the
PANAFTOSA Weekly Epidemiological Report, and we have publicly
apologised.
The unintended consequences of our error have been to demonstrate the
speed and effectiveness of the dissemination of outbreak reports by
Internet, and the speed of global response to Internet reporting.
--
Jack Woodall, Director ProMED-mail
***
Date: Wed, 13 Jan 1999 11:45:00 -0500
From: "#AFT:DIR" <aft_dir@panaftosa.ops-oms.org>
Subject: Noticia sobre aftosa en Argentina
Hemos leido la aclaracion sobre la
noticia de la ocurrencia de fiebre aftosa en la semana
49/98, en Argentina realizada por el Lic.
Gustavo Idigoras. Teniendo en cuenta que la noticia
original toma como fuente de informacion a PANAFTOSA, y
aunque Ud. aclara que se debio a un error de lectura de su
parte, no queda claro que PANAFTOSA no cometio errores en su
accion de informar los hechos. Ademas, hemos enviado el dia
11 de enero a PROMED@USA.HEALTHNET.ORG una aclaracion sobre
el hecho que hasta la fecha no ha sido distribuida, lo que
nos esta causando problemas. Le solicitamos que aclare a la
comunidad PROMED que PANAFTOSA no distribuyo informacion
erronea sobre el simulacro en Argentina. Agradecemos su
atencion a este pedido.
Josde German Rodriguez-Torrez, Director
"#AFT:DIR" <aft_dir@panaftosa.ops-oms.org>
.........................................jw
